						               													<description>On The Spot is the hilarious party game to hot seat your friends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You get to ask thing you would otherwise never know--you will finish this game closer to every single player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Original is rated R, and there is a family version rated PG.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player with the closest birthday get the red 'You Are On The Spot' first. Everyone takes 5 cards from the stack.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each round:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Start the 2 minute timer.&amp;#10;Begin grilling the player 'On The Spot'.&amp;#10;Moving clockwise, players ask 1 question at a time.&amp;#10;Discard the used card in front of the player 'On The Spot'.&amp;#10;Pick up a new card, so you always have 5.&amp;#10;Once time is up, the 'You Are On The Spot' card moves clockwise.&amp;#10;Rinse and repeat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Optional play to win: Save all the cards you answer. At the end, count your cards. Most questions answered wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;WARNING: You may learn too much about other players. EXTREMELY DEEP AND RAUNCHY. **This is a party game designed for a young adult audience** There is a different family version with wholesome questions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;NOTE I: You are allowed 1 skip no-questions-asked each round. Group decides consequences of skipping more than 1.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;NOTE II: Group is allowed to ask for 3 &amp;quot;story times&amp;quot; each round so player 'On The Spot' can further explain their answer. Pause the timer by laying it on its side during story times.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
